","Pentax is a little-known company that makes digital cameras. One of its waterproof cameras, the Pentax Optio WG-3 GPS, is a good camera to bring on any outdoor adventure. Sturdy, durable, and water-resistant to a depth of about 45 feet, the Pentax Optio WG-3 GPS has a unique design that makes it look more like a handheld radio than a digital camera. It also has a GPS geotagging function that allows you to imbed the images you take with your location information for future reference.","The Pentax Optio WG-3 GPS has good image quality with a 16-megapixel resolution. It also has a 4x optical zoom and a 7.2x digital zoom. The lens has a fairly wide F2.0 aperture that can close to about F4.9, so it takes good photos in low-light environments and underwater.  Instead of a bright flash at the top of the camera, the Pentax Optio WG-3 GPS has six little flash lights that surround the lens. We also love the GPS feature that allows you to geotag photos, see which direction the lens is facing as you take pictures and even use the camera as a compass.","Although we certainly don’t recommend throwing your camera around, this waterproof camera can sure take a beating. It is shock-proof up to 6 feet and water resistant to a depth of 45 feet. Since it’s waterproof, you can also rinse it off if it gets too dusty in the outdoors.","We especially love the shape of this underwater camera. It is unique, and the rubber siding makes it easy to hold and handle. It features a 3-inch LCD monitor on the back and a tripod mount on the bottom. The Pentax Optio WG-3 GPS comes in green and purple, but you can also purchase a non-GPS-enabled version in black or orange.","The Pentax Optio WG-3 GPS can take over 200 photos on a single battery charge. It comes with a rechargeable lithium-ion battery as well as a battery charger and charging cord, software, a USB connecting cable and a strap with a carabineer keychain. It also has 70MB of internal memory so you can store your photos and videos directly on the camera.","Pentax&#39;s support section can be a little hard to navigate, but its offerings are helpful when you finally find what you&#39;re looking for. The company has live chat support, which is a very useful feature, but its website does not have any FAQs. You can also contact Pentax by email or telephone."]},"id":"01174ec0-0bef-480d-ac91-648b460cccdc","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"663fa29c-184b-4e40-84f7-028e522706ad","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["We really like the Pentax Optio WG-3 GPS waterproof camera. The photos are a good quality and it’s easy enough to use. The tough design, coupled with the image quality and underwater capabilities, makes it a great gift for avid hikers, backpackers and general adventurers who like to document their experiences."]},"id":"84648e31-1f29-47ac-80dc-567254bf452f","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_54146","url":"/pentax-waterproof-camera-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"suzanne-humphries","url":"/author/suzanne-humphries","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","name":"Suzanne Humphries","dateModified":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","id":"5Cbzn8X4VHCDchbqEBVidP","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2012-01-05T20:34:08Z","datePublished":"2012-01-05T20:34:08Z","name":"Pentax Optio WG-3 GPS","synopsis":"Editor’s Note: This product has been removed from our side-by-side comparison because it has been replaced by another product.","review":{"rating":86,"verdict":"With a 16MP resolution and water-resistant depth of 45 feet, this camera is a smart pick.","pros":["The Pentax Optio WG-3 GPS is durable and has a unique and easy-to-grip design."],"cons":["It&#8217;s a little bigger than other cameras in this category."]},"strapline":"Editor’s Note: This product has been removed from our side-by-side comparison because it has been replaced by another product.","language":"en","dateModified":"2012-01-05T20:34:08Z",